'''Rosalind Polly Blakesley''' (née Gray) is reader in Russian and European art and fellow of [[Pembroke College, Cambridge|Pembroke College]], University of Cambridge.<ref>[http://www.hoart.cam.ac.uk/people/rpg27@cam.ac.uk Dr Rosalind Polly Blakesley MA DPhil.] Department of History of Art, University of Cambridge. Retrieved 20 December 2016.</ref> She is a trustee of the [[National Portrait Gallery, London|National Portrait Gallery]].<ref>[https://www.gov.uk/government/news/prime-minister-reappoints-3-trustees-of-the-national-portrait-gallery Prime Minister reappoints 3 Trustees of the National Portrait Gallery.] Gov.uk. Retrieved 20 December 2016.</ref>
==Selected publications== * ''Russian Genre Painting in the Nineteenth Century''. [[Clarendon Press]], Oxford, 2000. ([[Oxford Historical Monographs]]) (under her maiden name of Rosalind P. Gray) * ''An Imperial Collection: Women Artists from the State Hermitage Museum''. 2003. (co-editor and contributor) * ''The Arts and Crafts Movement''. Phaidon, London, 2006. * ''Russian Art and the West: a Century of Dialogue in Painting, Architecture and the Decorative Arts''. 2007. (co-editor and contributor) * ''From Realism to the Silver Age: New Studies in Russian Artistic Culture''. 2014. (co-editor and contributor) * ''The Russian Canvas: Painting in Imperial Russia, 1757-1878''. [[Yale University Press]], New Haven, 2016. {{ISBN|978-0300184372}}
